[b]Step 2![/b]
Close [b]Cooking.java[/b] and open your [b]client.java[/b].
Now your going to make [b]Cooking.java[/b] have an effect.

Search your [b]client.java[/b] for

[code=java]case 192:[/code]

And you will find something like 

[code=java]		case 192:
			junk = inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA();
			int UsedOnObjectID = inStream.readUnsignedWordBigEndian();
			int UsedOnY = inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA();
			int ItemSlot = (inStream.readSignedWordBigEndianA() - 128);
			int UsedOnX = inStream.readUnsignedWordBigEndianA();
			int ItemID = inStream.readUnsignedWord();
			if (!playerHasItem(ItemID))
				break;
			if (!antiHax())
				break;
			if (UsedOnObjectID == 3994) {
				for (int fi = 0; fi < misc.smelt_frame.length; fi++)
				sendFrame246(misc.smelt_frame[fi], 150, misc.smelt_bars[fi]);
				sendFrame164(2400);
			}[/code]

Under the last bracelet ([b]}[/b]) is where the last code should be placed.
Before giving you the snippet I'll explain it:

[code=java]			if (UsedOnObjectID == 12269 && ItemID == 317) {
				faceNPC(UsedOnObjectID);
				TurnPlayerTo(UsedOnX, UsedOnY);
				Cooking.Cooking(playerId, #);
			}[/code]

If [b]UsedOnObjectID[/b] and [b]ItemID[/b] equals to [b]12269[/b] (Cooking Range) and [b]317[/b] (Raw Shrimp) then the player will face to the object you used the item on and cook what you used. The [b][color=red]#[/b] is the array index.

If you dont know what number it should be take a look at this:

Example 1:

[code=java]int[] Array = {0, 1, 2, 3, 4, ..};[/code]

[b]Array[0][/b] would return [b]0[/b]
[b]Array[4][/b] would return [b]4[/b]

Example 2:

[code=java]int[] Array = {60, 70, 80, 90, 100, ..};[/code]

[b]Array[0][/b] would return [b]60[/b]
[b]Array[4][/b] would return [b]100[/b]

Now you know how to edit and add food types into the 
[code=java]	public static int[][] CookingArray = {
		{1, 30, 40, 45, 80}, // Cooking Level Needed
		{317, 359, 377, 371, 383}, // Raw Food Id
		{315, 361, 379, 373, 385}, // Cooked Food Id
		{323, 367, 381, 375, 387}, // Burnt Food Id
		{30, 100, 120, 140, 210}, // Experience * ExpRate
		{15, 65, 68, 86, 100}, // Noburn Level (Without Cooking Gauntlets)
		{15, 65, 74, 86, 94}, // Noburn Level (With Cooking Gauntlets)
	};[/code]

Let me explain what this does (look code below)
[code=java]Cooking.Cooking(playerId, #);[/code]

It calls the [code=java]public static void Cooking(int playerId, int ArrayIndex) {[/code] that you put into the [b]Cooking.java[/b]-file.

The first Cooking is the class' name.

